---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Book Lore"
  description="What Book Lore is, what it isn't, and how it fits in the oriz family."
>
  <header class="container-prose page-head">
    <p class="eyebrow"><a href="/">Book Lore</a> / About</p>
    <h1>About Book Lore</h1>
  </header>

  <article class="container-prose prose">
    <p class="lede">
      <strong>Book Lore</strong> is a free atlas of structured book summaries.
      Each entry is split into four parts — overview, content map, critical
      analysis, and narration script — authored as MDX and published as plain
      static HTML.
    </p>

    <h2>How it works</h2>
    <p>
      Books are organised into a two-level taxonomy: a top category (e.g.
      <em>Mind, Brain and Behavior</em>) and a discipline subcategory (e.g.
      <em>Learning Science and Education</em>). Browse by
      <a href="/categories/">category</a>, search the
      <a href="/books/">full list</a>, or sign in to bookmark and take notes.
    </p>

    <h2>What Book Lore isn't</h2>
    <p>
      It is <em>not</em> a substitute for reading the book. Summaries are
      commentary — opinionated, structured, and useful as a map; the territory
      still belongs to the original author. Quoted excerpts fall under fair
      use / fair dealing.
    </p>

    <h2>Part of the oriz family</h2>
    <p>
      Book Lore is one of ten sites under <a href="https://oriz.in">oriz.in</a> —
      a free family of static sites by Chirag Singhal. Sign-in is shared:
      one account at <a href="https://oriz.in/account/">oriz.in/account</a>
      works on every <code>*.oriz.in</code> site.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a> or
      use the <a href="/contact/">contact form</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-head { padding-block: 3rem 1.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-border); }
  .eyebrow { color: var(--color-fg-muted); font-size: 0.8125rem; margin: 0 0 0.5rem; }
  .eyebrow a { color: var(--color-fg-muted); text-decoration: none; }
  h1 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem); font-weight: 600; letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin: 0; }
  .prose { padding-block: 2.5rem 4rem; color: var(--color-prose); line-height: 1.75; font-size: 1.0625rem; }
  .prose .lede { font-size: 1.1875rem; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 0 0 2rem; }
  .prose h2 { font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-fg); margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 1.25rem; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent); }
  .prose code { background: var(--color-bg-muted); padding: 0.125em 0.375em; border-radius: 0.25rem; font-size: 0.875em; }
</style>
